The proof relies on the fact that for an involution on a finite set, the parity of the cardinality of the set is the same as the parity of the number of fixed points. Since we established that the set $U_k$ (which has the same cardinality as $T_k$) has exactly one fixed point under the involution `secondInvo k`, its cardinality must be odd.

```lean
